Screenshot showing using the new find command to find the phrase toml in a table
In 0.37, you now have access to a new 
``find``
 command, which can help you quickly look for data across all columns in a table.
You can still reach your system's 
``find``
 command using 
``^``
 by typing 
``^find``
.
